    "what_description": "Echinacea angustifolia is a perennial plant that belongs to the family Asteraceae. It has a taproot system and grows up to 1 meter in height, with a spread of about 60 cm. The plant has narrow, linear leaves that are usually 10-20 cm long and 2-5 mm wide, arranged oppositely on the stem. The flowers are daisy-like, with a pink to purple corolla, 3-5 cm in diameter, and a prominent, drooping stamen. Echinacea angustifolia is native to the prairies of central North America.",
